---
import { thresholds } from "../../lib/monitoring";
import AppLayout from "../../layouts/AppLayout.astro";
---
<AppLayout title="Settings" description="Workspace settings">
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/45">Workspace configuration</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">Settings</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-white/70">
        Core operating thresholds and collaboration settings for the MVP. Team roles and automated
        notifications are staged as follow-up features.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-4 xl:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/45">Team</p>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">Access control</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-white/65">
          Role-based access is coming soon. Managers, operators, and vendors will each get scoped views and
          approval flows.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6 xl:col-span-2">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/45">Thresholds</p>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">Water quality targets</h2>
        <div class="mt-5 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <label class="space-y-2">
            <span class="text-sm text-white/75">pH minimum</span>
            <input
              type="number"
              value={thresholds.phMin}
              class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 px-4 py-3 text-sm text-white outline-none"
            />
          </label>
          <label class="space-y-2">
            <span class="text-sm text-white/75">pH maximum</span>
            <input
              type="number"
              value={thresholds.phMax}
              class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 px-4 py-3 text-sm text-white outline-none"
            />
          </label>
          <label class="space-y-2">
            <span class="text-sm text-white/75">Chlorine minimum</span>
            <input
              type="number"
              value={thresholds.chlorineMin}
              class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 px-4 py-3 text-sm text-white outline-none"
            />
          </label>
          <label class="space-y-2">
            <span class="text-sm text-white/75">Chlorine maximum</span>
            <input
              type="number"
              value={thresholds.chlorineMax}
              class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 px-4 py-3 text-sm text-white outline-none"
            />
          </label>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6 xl:col-span-3">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/45">Notifications</p>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">Dispatch channels</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-white/65">
          Email and SMS escalation rules are coming soon. The backend connector will dispatch chemistry and
          safety exceptions to the right team once it is enabled.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</AppLayout>
